ActFinancial Administration Act
Business Development Bank of Canada Act
SubjectOrder Designating the Minister for International Trade (1) as the Designated Minister for the purposes of the Business Development Bank of Canada Act; and (2) as the appropriate Minister with respect to the Business Development Bank of Canada for the purposes of the Financial Administration Act
PrecisOrder (1) repealing Order in Council P.C. 2018-1020 of July 18, 2018; (2) designating the MINISTER OF INTERNATIONAL TRADE, a member of the Queen’s Privy Council for Canada, as the Designated Minister for the purposes of the BUSINESS DEVELOPMENT BANK OF CANADA ACT; and (3) designating the MINISTER OF INTERNATIONAL TRADE, a member of the Queen’s Privy Council for Canada, as the appropriate Minister with respect to the Business Development Bank of Canada for the purposes of the FINANCIAL ADMINISTRATION ACT.
